The paper discusses the recovery of signals from incomplete and inaccurate measurements, which is a central topic in compressed sensing. The use of Basis Pursuit and the analysis of stability and accuracy of the recovered signal are common themes in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Sound and Image Processing (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
